Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Combine all muffin ingredients except flour, sour cream, powdered sugar and orange marmalade in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes). Add flour and sour cream; continue beating until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes). Spoon batter into greased mini muffin pans, filling cups 3/4 full. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes; remove from pans. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.